  <prompt>
    Execute an end-to-end UI test for the EmailComposer Code Page in `mode=reply`. Open a Code Page URL with `mode=reply&id={existing-record-guid}`, verify the form is pre-filled per FR-11:
    - `to` = original record's `from` address
    - `subject` starts with `Re: ` (not duplicated if already prefixed)
    - `body` wraps the original body with a divider
    - `sprk_inreplyto` lookup is stamped on the new record when Send is clicked

    Use the `ui-test` skill. Verify zero console errors. Verify dark mode smoke per ADR-021.

    Depends on task 003 (Internet-Message-Id capture) â€” the parent record must have `sprk_internetmessageid` populated for reply-thread closure verification (FR-22).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke UI test engineer. Familiar with reply-mode semantics (FR-11), `sprk_inreplyto` schema, and `IncomingAssociationResolver` reply-thread matching (R2 implementation).
  </role>

  <goal>
    UI test pass for reply mode. Test results in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/043-ui-test-reply.md`. Verifies prefill correctness + `sprk_inreplyto` stamp post-Send.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-11: reply mode pre-fills new compose from an existing `sprk_communication`. `to` = original `from`; `cc` blank; `subject` = `Re: ${original.subject}` (no double-prefix); `body` wraps original with a divider; `attachments` not carried; `associations` carried; `sprk_inreplyto` stamped on new record pointing to original.

      Post-send verification: query Dataverse for the new `sprk_communication` record (the reply) and confirm its `sprk_inreplyto` field references the original record's GUID.

      Depends on task 003 (Internet-Message-Id capture) ensuring the original record has `sprk_internetmessageid` populated â€” required for reply-thread closure verification per FR-22 + ADR-024.
    </background>
